title: Nana's Stew
author: DeepCopy
pages:
#- §1§lMaking a proper Stew.§0
§1§l----------------§0
§0
§0I'm sure you've heard it before, but a stew must be made from only the finest ingredients.§0
§0
§0Well, my grandmother shared this recipe with me when I was a young boy, and it's never
#- done me wrong.§0
§0
§0First, take a fine helping of potatos, carrots, and seeds, and let those cook for a bit. Add in a couple brown mushrooms and a generous portion of browned beef tips, and let them all cook down together for a good 30 minutes.
#- Enjoy with a fine Beer or Ale and be sure to tell ol' nan thank you when someday you see her in the beyond.
#- 